Class systemManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • systemManager
  • public class systemManager
extends java.lang.Object
    The systemManager class is responsible for managing the overall system and interacting with the store, customers, and admins. It provides methods for registering new customers and admins, logging in existing customers and admins, and loading data from CSV files.

      • register

        public void register()
        Registers a new customer by prompting the user for their name, email, phone number, password, and address. Creates a new Customer object and adds it to the store's list of customers.

        public void registerAdmin()
        Registers a new admin by prompting the user for their name, email, phone number, and password. Creates a new Admin object and adds it to the store's list of admins.

      • loginCustomer

        public Customer loginCustomer()

      • loginAdmin
